{#-
Gemma-family EXL2 chat template (repo-local, EXL2-compatible).

Why this exists:
- Gemma instruct models are sensitive to `<start_of_turn>` / `<end_of_turn>` markers.
- The model's tokenizer_config `chat_template` uses `raise_exception(...)` which our minimal Jinja environment may not provide.

Behavior:
- If the first message is `role=system`, inject it as a prefix into the first user turn (matching Gemma tokenizer templates).
- Map assistant role to `model`.
- Wrap every message in:
    <start_of_turn>{role}\n{content}<end_of_turn>\n
- Sanitize assistant history: if an assistant message contains `</think>`, only replay content after the final `</think>`.
- Add generation prompt:
    <start_of_turn>model\n
-#}

{{ bos_token }}
{%- if messages and messages[0]["role"] == "system" -%}
  {%- set first_user_prefix = (messages[0]["content"] | trim) ~ "\n\n" -%}
  {%- set loop_messages = messages[1:] -%}
{%- else -%}
  {%- set first_user_prefix = "" -%}
  {%- set loop_messages = messages -%}
{%- endif -%}

{%- for message in loop_messages -%}
  {%- if message["role"] == "assistant" -%}
    {%- set role = "model" -%}
  {%- else -%}
    {%- set role = message["role"] -%}
  {%- endif -%}
<start_of_turn>{{ role }}
  {%- if loop.first and role == "user" and first_user_prefix -%}
{{ first_user_prefix }}
  {%- endif -%}
  {%- if message["content"] is string -%}
    {%- if role == "model" -%}
      {%- set content = (message["content"] | trim) -%}
      {%- if "</think>" in content -%}
        {%- set content = content.split("</think>")[-1] -%}
      {%- endif -%}
{{ content }}
    {%- else -%}
{{ message["content"] | trim }}
    {%- endif -%}
  {%- else -%}
{{ message["content"] }}
  {%- endif -%}
<end_of_turn>
{%- endfor -%}

{%- if add_generation_prompt -%}
<start_of_turn>model
{%- endif -%}

